I run my Atlassian Confluence server over the internet, it is for open source script development and therefore does not need to be secured. Furthermore I use http as I can then use an (affordable) Content Delivery Network rather than running over HTTPS.

However for basic system and user security I really need the ability to force SSL only for login functions of Confluence.

To this day I have achieved this 99% through htaccess rewrites however it can sometimes prove to be buggy and would be far better to have a simple checkbox which said "Force logins over SSL" but ran the rest of the application in HTTP mode.

