Here's scenario on how and why this feature is crucial for some organization:

Organization have 2 group of user with the name GROUPA , GROUPB GROUPC. One of the user group GROUPA have the permission to create personal spaces and spaces however they are not suppose to show those space content to GROUPB. The space administrator from GROUPA can end up choosing a wrong group to assign permission  (GROUPB) which could potential compromise their company data.

Therefore it is important for the system administrator to restrict the group or user that could be added into a space by default to prevent this matter.

